verses.text:
The hands of Zerubbabel have laid the foundation of this house;
his hands shall also finish it; and thou shalt know that the \nd LORD\nd*
of hosts hath sent me unto you.

And it came to pass in the fourth year of king Darius, \add that\add*
the word of the \nd LORD\nd* came unto Zechariah in the fourth \add day\add*
of the ninth month, \add even\add* in Chisleu;

\add There is\add* a voice of the howling of the shepherds;
for their glory is spoiled: a voice of the roaring of young lions;
for the pride of Jordan is spoiled.

Whose possessors slay them, and hold themselves not guilty:
and they that sell them say, Blessed \add be\add* the \nd LORD\nd*;
for I am rich: and their own shepherds pity them not.
